00:00:31.059 --> 00:00:34.470 align:middle line:10%
>> The dark knight of the soul
is defined as a time that comes

00:00:34.470 --> 00:00:37.760 align:middle line:10%
in almost everyone's life--
unless you're very fortunate--

00:00:37.760 --> 00:00:41.630 align:middle line:10%
when everything that you've
ever loved or held dear is gone.

00:00:41.630 --> 00:00:43.970 align:middle line:10%
You might come home someday
and your family, your job,

00:00:43.970 --> 00:00:45.740 align:middle line:10%
your house, your car,
everything is gone.

00:00:45.740 --> 00:00:48.590 align:middle line:10%
And in that moment, we're
pushed to the very edge

00:00:48.590 --> 00:00:49.730 align:middle line:10%
of who we believe we are.

00:00:49.730 --> 00:00:55.640 align:middle line:10%
>> Is it possible that you and
I are praying the wrong way?

00:00:55.640 --> 00:00:57.390 align:middle line:84%
I don't know, sometimes
I wonder because I

00:00:57.390 --> 00:00:59.280 align:middle line:90%
don't get my prayers answered.

00:00:59.280 --> 00:01:01.860 align:middle line:84%
We're going to find out
more about that today.

00:01:01.860 --> 00:01:05.280 align:middle line:84%
We have Gregg Braden who
is the author of "Walking

00:01:05.280 --> 00:01:07.800 align:middle line:84%
Between The Worlds,"
and we're going

00:01:07.800 --> 00:01:10.867 align:middle line:90%
to talk about prayer today.

00:01:10.867 --> 00:01:11.700 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to the show.

00:01:11.700 --> 00:01:12.730 align:middle line:90%
>> It's a pleasure to be here.

00:01:12.730 --> 00:01:13.290 align:middle line:90%
Thank you, Corinne.

00:01:13.290 --> 00:01:15.082 align:middle line:84%
>> First of all, before
we get into prayer,

00:01:15.082 --> 00:01:17.790 align:middle line:84%
I just wanted to get everybody's
attention there because we all

00:01:17.790 --> 00:01:19.500 align:middle line:84%
worry about whether
we're doing it right.

00:01:19.500 --> 00:01:20.500 align:middle line:90%
>> You got my attention.

00:01:20.500 --> 00:01:22.170 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:01:22.170 --> 00:01:24.690 align:middle line:84%
Tell us a little bit about
yourself and your work,

00:01:24.690 --> 00:01:28.005 align:middle line:84%
and what you're particularly
interested in now.

00:01:28.005 --> 00:01:32.730 align:middle line:10%
>> My passion in this moment
is finding the language

00:01:32.730 --> 00:01:37.590 align:middle line:10%
and the means to share what I
believe is a very relevant body

00:01:37.590 --> 00:01:41.400 align:middle line:10%
of information, although it is
very ancient at the same time,

00:01:41.400 --> 00:01:44.760 align:middle line:10%
some of the information was lost
to the west over 1,700 years

00:01:44.760 --> 00:01:45.600 align:middle line:10%
ago.

00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:47.430 align:middle line:84%
Bringing this body
of information

00:01:47.430 --> 00:01:51.360 align:middle line:84%
to bear, to provide a context
and framework within which

00:01:51.360 --> 00:01:55.440 align:middle line:84%
to view all of the outrageous
social, political, economic,

00:01:55.440 --> 00:01:58.590 align:middle line:84%
natural phenomenon that we're
seeing in our world today.

00:01:58.590 --> 00:02:01.230 align:middle line:84%
And to move through
those changes with grace.

00:02:01.230 --> 00:02:03.102 align:middle line:90%
>> What was lost, Gregg?

00:02:03.102 --> 00:02:06.620 align:middle line:84%
>> 1,700 years ago,
in the year 325 AD,

00:02:06.620 --> 00:02:11.630 align:middle line:84%
there were tremendous pieces of
our most sacred heritage that

00:02:11.630 --> 00:02:14.120 align:middle line:90%
were taken from our texts.

00:02:14.120 --> 00:02:16.880 align:middle line:84%
And clearly, this
transcends religion.

00:02:16.880 --> 00:02:19.520 align:middle line:84%
This is historical information,
although much of it

00:02:19.520 --> 00:02:22.670 align:middle line:84%
was recorded in what later
became biblical texts.

00:02:22.670 --> 00:02:24.320 align:middle line:84%
We know that at
least 25 books were

00:02:24.320 --> 00:02:28.910 align:middle line:84%
lost from our biblical text, at
least 20 additional documents.

00:02:28.910 --> 00:02:30.830 align:middle line:84%
And the ones that
were left were poorly

00:02:30.830 --> 00:02:33.380 align:middle line:84%
translated into the
languages of the west.

00:02:33.380 --> 00:02:35.180 align:middle line:84%
At later time, I
like to call it maybe

00:02:35.180 --> 00:02:37.710 align:middle line:84%
we got the Reader's
Digest condensed version

00:02:37.710 --> 00:02:39.710 align:middle line:84%
because you can literally
take the ancient texts

00:02:39.710 --> 00:02:42.080 align:middle line:84%
and our modern version,
place them side by side,

00:02:42.080 --> 00:02:44.330 align:middle line:84%
and see what we may have the
first, the last sentence,

00:02:44.330 --> 00:02:48.230 align:middle line:84%
and the good stuff in between
in many cases is missing.

00:02:48.230 --> 00:02:49.373 align:middle line:90%
>> So where is it?

00:02:49.373 --> 00:02:50.290 align:middle line:90%
Is it being found now?

00:02:50.290 --> 00:02:51.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, it's interesting.

00:02:51.530 --> 00:02:53.697 align:middle line:84%
It's the basis of
the Dead Sea Scrolls,

00:02:53.697 --> 00:02:55.280 align:middle line:84%
maybe one of the
reasons why we're not

00:02:55.280 --> 00:02:58.610 align:middle line:84%
being allowed to see the
scrolls, the translations,

00:02:58.610 --> 00:02:59.900 align:middle line:90%
and their entirety.

00:02:59.900 --> 00:03:03.080 align:middle line:84%
Some of them were
copyrighted in 1993.

00:03:03.080 --> 00:03:05.360 align:middle line:90%
It is also found--

00:03:05.360 --> 00:03:09.050 align:middle line:84%
a body of information this
solid and this relevant,

00:03:09.050 --> 00:03:12.170 align:middle line:84%
I knew would never be
left to a single people

00:03:12.170 --> 00:03:13.040 align:middle line:90%
in the single text.

00:03:13.040 --> 00:03:15.438 align:middle line:84%
I expected to see it in
many different places.

00:03:15.438 --> 00:03:16.730 align:middle line:90%
And as we've searched, we have.

00:03:16.730 --> 00:03:19.070 align:middle line:84%
We've found that in the great
libraries of St. Catherine's

00:03:19.070 --> 00:03:19.940 align:middle line:90%
Monastery in Mt.

00:03:19.940 --> 00:03:20.900 align:middle line:90%
Sinai.

00:03:20.900 --> 00:03:22.100 align:middle line:90%
We've found it in Ethiopia.

00:03:22.100 --> 00:03:25.470 align:middle line:84%
We've found it certainly
in the Nag Hammadi Library.

00:03:25.470 --> 00:03:28.370 align:middle line:84%
We've found it in indigenous
North and South American

00:03:28.370 --> 00:03:32.550 align:middle line:84%
traditions, as well as in some
of the great libraries of what

00:03:32.550 --> 00:03:34.170 align:middle line:90%
today are Central Tibet.

00:03:34.170 --> 00:03:37.070 align:middle line:84%
>> Tell us about your
recent trip to Tibet.

00:03:37.070 --> 00:03:37.870 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:03:37.870 --> 00:03:41.530 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it was an
amazing journey.

00:03:41.530 --> 00:03:45.490 align:middle line:84%
In April of this year, of '98,
I had the opportunity to journey

00:03:45.490 --> 00:03:49.060 align:middle line:84%
with a small group
into Central Tibet

00:03:49.060 --> 00:03:51.250 align:middle line:84%
for the purpose
of what I believed

00:03:51.250 --> 00:03:56.080 align:middle line:84%
would be to identify fragments
of this ancient wisdom that

00:03:56.080 --> 00:03:58.240 align:middle line:84%
had been carried in
the Tibetan traditions

00:03:58.240 --> 00:04:00.910 align:middle line:84%
and preserved through
their isolation.

00:04:00.910 --> 00:04:03.010 align:middle line:84%
The Ancient Essenes,
the authors of Dead Sea

00:04:03.010 --> 00:04:06.430 align:middle line:84%
Scrolls in the
Qumran Area, we know

00:04:06.430 --> 00:04:09.940 align:middle line:84%
dispersed 500 years
after the crucifixion

00:04:09.940 --> 00:04:12.160 align:middle line:84%
into many parts of the world,
and Tibet was certainly

00:04:12.160 --> 00:04:13.870 align:middle line:90%
one of those.

00:04:13.870 --> 00:04:17.050 align:middle line:84%
The intent was rather than
speculating through a written

00:04:17.050 --> 00:04:21.670 align:middle line:84%
text what may be inferred
was to actually speak

00:04:21.670 --> 00:04:24.670 align:middle line:84%
to those people who were
living those traditions

00:04:24.670 --> 00:04:28.330 align:middle line:84%
and saying to them in the
matter of prayer, for example.

00:04:28.330 --> 00:04:31.780 align:middle line:84%
Now that we have seen your
tones, and your chants,

00:04:31.780 --> 00:04:35.335 align:middle line:84%
and your mudras that you're
doing on the outside,

00:04:35.335 --> 00:04:37.420 align:middle line:84%
what happened to
you on the inside?

00:04:37.420 --> 00:04:40.030 align:middle line:84%
What were you doing
when we witnessed those?

00:04:40.030 --> 00:04:42.100 align:middle line:84%
And through our guides
and our interpreters,

00:04:42.100 --> 00:04:44.320 align:middle line:84%
there were 15 monasteries
and nunneries.

00:04:44.320 --> 00:04:48.070 align:middle line:84%
We had the opportunity to
interact with these people.

00:04:48.070 --> 00:04:52.330 align:middle line:84%
And lo and behold, they
validated my suspicion

00:04:52.330 --> 00:04:54.820 align:middle line:84%
that they were actually
living fragments

00:04:54.820 --> 00:04:58.210 align:middle line:84%
of these Ancient Essene
traditions, this wisdom that

00:04:58.210 --> 00:04:59.830 align:middle line:90%
was lost 1,700 years ago.

00:04:59.830 --> 00:05:01.855 align:middle line:90%
>> Were there any texts there?

00:05:01.855 --> 00:05:05.560 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, yes, there
were many texts.

00:05:05.560 --> 00:05:10.025 align:middle line:84%
We were there three weeks,
altitudes over 17,500 feet

00:05:10.025 --> 00:05:10.825 align:middle line:90%
in the Himalayas.

00:05:10.825 --> 00:05:11.770 align:middle line:90%
>> Slept a lot.

00:05:11.770 --> 00:05:15.960 align:middle line:84%
>> I live 8,000 feet in
the northern New Mexico

00:05:15.960 --> 00:05:16.760 align:middle line:90%
in the mountains.

00:05:16.760 --> 00:05:20.680 align:middle line:84%
And this 17,000 feet,
it's a different world.

00:05:20.680 --> 00:05:24.340 align:middle line:84%
What we discovered,
some of the highest,

00:05:24.340 --> 00:05:27.970 align:middle line:84%
least disturbed monasteries
through a series of very

00:05:27.970 --> 00:05:30.670 align:middle line:84%
heartfelt interactions with
the monks that were there,

00:05:30.670 --> 00:05:33.550 align:middle line:84%
they shared with
us their libraries

00:05:33.550 --> 00:05:36.820 align:middle line:84%
that actually of all the
things that Tibetans represent

00:05:36.820 --> 00:05:39.140 align:middle line:84%
to us as anchors of
compassion, love, and wisdom,

00:05:39.140 --> 00:05:41.620 align:middle line:84%
they're tremendous
record keepers.

00:05:41.620 --> 00:05:43.330 align:middle line:84%
And they don't
judge the records.

00:05:43.330 --> 00:05:46.180 align:middle line:84%
They have Christian records
as well as Buddhist records

00:05:46.180 --> 00:05:49.960 align:middle line:84%
as well as the records of
their ancient traditions.

00:05:49.960 --> 00:05:53.330 align:middle line:84%
They didn't lose that
information 1,700 years ago.

00:05:53.330 --> 00:05:55.960 align:middle line:84%
So from their
perspective, they know

00:05:55.960 --> 00:05:58.480 align:middle line:84%
that this is a rare precious
moment in human history

00:05:58.480 --> 00:06:01.150 align:middle line:90%
and that compassion is so key.

00:06:01.150 --> 00:06:03.280 align:middle line:84%
And that there is an
ancient technology that

00:06:03.280 --> 00:06:07.240 align:middle line:84%
lives within each of us
that has a direct impact,

00:06:07.240 --> 00:06:09.550 align:middle line:84%
a direct linear
measurable impact

00:06:09.550 --> 00:06:12.580 align:middle line:84%
on the outcome of the events
in the world around us.

00:06:12.580 --> 00:06:15.740 align:middle line:84%
Today, we call that
technology prayer.

00:06:15.740 --> 00:06:19.140 align:middle line:84%
>> So this is what was
in the text that we lost?

00:06:19.140 --> 00:06:20.470 align:middle line:90%
>> Many of the texts.

00:06:20.470 --> 00:06:21.832 align:middle line:90%
And when I speak about prayer.

00:06:21.832 --> 00:06:23.290 align:middle line:84%
Prayer, it's a very
personal thing.

00:06:23.290 --> 00:06:25.207 align:middle line:84%
It means different things
to different people.

00:06:25.207 --> 00:06:29.230 align:middle line:84%
Western researchers today
identify four modes of prayer

00:06:29.230 --> 00:06:32.440 align:middle line:84%
that we use either alone or
in some combination with one

00:06:32.440 --> 00:06:33.550 align:middle line:90%
another.

00:06:33.550 --> 00:06:35.530 align:middle line:84%
Ancient traditions
have always described

00:06:35.530 --> 00:06:38.340 align:middle line:84%
another mode that didn't seem
to fit into any of those.

00:06:38.340 --> 00:06:39.830 align:middle line:84%
And it led me to
ask the question,

00:06:39.830 --> 00:06:40.870 align:middle line:90%
is there another mode?

00:06:40.870 --> 00:06:44.020 align:middle line:84%
Is there a fifth mode
or lost mode of prayer?

00:06:44.020 --> 00:06:46.060 align:middle line:84%
From our time in
Tibetan from these texts

00:06:46.060 --> 00:06:49.360 align:middle line:84%
and the ancient scholars, what
we know as the answer to that

00:06:49.360 --> 00:06:50.635 align:middle line:90%
is yes.

00:06:50.635 --> 00:06:51.820 align:middle line:90%
>> But the way--

00:06:51.820 --> 00:06:54.400 align:middle line:84%
we found that the
way I pray if I say,

00:06:54.400 --> 00:06:56.470 align:middle line:90%
God, I know you're very busy.

00:06:56.470 --> 00:06:59.930 align:middle line:90%
So I know this is the problem.

00:06:59.930 --> 00:07:02.320 align:middle line:84%
And by the way, God,
this is the answer.

00:07:02.320 --> 00:07:03.180 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:07:03.180 --> 00:07:05.920 align:middle line:84%
>> [LAUGHS] And by the way, I
don't want to bother you with.

00:07:05.920 --> 00:07:07.990 align:middle line:90%
Just get it for me.

00:07:07.990 --> 00:07:10.060 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's the
way most of us pray.

00:07:10.060 --> 00:07:11.170 align:middle line:90%
We tell God what to do.

00:07:11.170 --> 00:07:14.230 align:middle line:84%
>> In the Western traditions,
many of our prayers are prayers

00:07:14.230 --> 00:07:17.380 align:middle line:84%
of asking where we are
conditioned to feel powerless

00:07:17.380 --> 00:07:24.800 align:middle line:84%
in a situation or helpless and
we ask for divine intervention

00:07:24.800 --> 00:07:27.990 align:middle line:84%
or we petition that
something come to pass.

00:07:27.990 --> 00:07:30.340 align:middle line:84%
The four modes of prayer
is the colloquial prayer,

00:07:30.340 --> 00:07:33.190 align:middle line:84%
a petitionary prayer,
a ritualistic prayer,

00:07:33.190 --> 00:07:35.050 align:middle line:90%
and meditative prayer.

00:07:35.050 --> 00:07:40.510 align:middle line:84%
And this mode of prayer is so
clearly different than those.

00:07:40.510 --> 00:07:45.850 align:middle line:84%
It's a prayer that is based
in the emotion and the feeling

00:07:45.850 --> 00:07:49.660 align:middle line:84%
that the prayer has already
come to pass rather than asking

00:07:49.660 --> 00:07:51.640 align:middle line:90%
that something happen.

00:07:51.640 --> 00:07:54.220 align:middle line:84%
I'll back up just a little
bit and give some examples.

00:07:54.220 --> 00:07:58.210 align:middle line:84%
When we're asking that something
come to pass, please God,

00:07:58.210 --> 00:08:00.760 align:middle line:84%
let my car get to the
Texaco station at 2 o'clock

00:08:00.760 --> 00:08:03.070 align:middle line:84%
in the morning before
it runs out of gas.

00:08:03.070 --> 00:08:04.840 align:middle line:84%
This once, I'll
never do this again.

00:08:04.840 --> 00:08:07.210 align:middle line:90%
OK, that's an asking.

00:08:07.210 --> 00:08:11.530 align:middle line:84%
We're implying that it
doesn't have gas in the tank.

00:08:11.530 --> 00:08:13.570 align:middle line:84%
So in our asking, our
prayers for global peace,

00:08:13.570 --> 00:08:16.720 align:middle line:84%
we're saying maybe that
peace doesn't exist right now

00:08:16.720 --> 00:08:19.870 align:middle line:84%
and perhaps unknowingly
perpetuating that state

00:08:19.870 --> 00:08:21.710 align:middle line:90%
of affairs on the one hand.

00:08:21.710 --> 00:08:24.550 align:middle line:84%
The lost mode of prayer,
rather than using the logic

00:08:24.550 --> 00:08:27.895 align:middle line:84%
in the thought, invites us to
come from a place of emotion

00:08:27.895 --> 00:08:29.770 align:middle line:84%
that our prayers have
already been fulfilled,

00:08:29.770 --> 00:08:31.840 align:middle line:84%
that peace already
exists in the world,

00:08:31.840 --> 00:08:33.985 align:middle line:84%
that gas is already
in that tank.

00:08:33.985 --> 00:08:36.789 align:middle line:84%
>> This is interesting because
what you're saying is that

00:08:36.789 --> 00:08:43.080 align:middle line:84%
the universe is pretty
neutral, that it will answer us

00:08:43.080 --> 00:08:45.480 align:middle line:84%
according to the vibration
that we put out there.

00:08:45.480 --> 00:08:48.690 align:middle line:84%
>> This is the beginning
of an ancient technology.

00:08:48.690 --> 00:08:51.480 align:middle line:84%
It was relegated to priesthood
into the mystery schools

00:08:51.480 --> 00:08:52.778 align:middle line:90%
1,700 years ago.

00:08:52.778 --> 00:08:55.320 align:middle line:84%
Prior to that time, apparently,
the average man in the street

00:08:55.320 --> 00:08:56.990 align:middle line:90%
knew this.

00:08:56.990 --> 00:08:59.280 align:middle line:84%
And for whatever
reason, the year 325 AD,

00:08:59.280 --> 00:09:00.960 align:middle line:90%
we began to forget.

00:09:00.960 --> 00:09:03.270 align:middle line:84%
And my question is
when did we begin

00:09:03.270 --> 00:09:05.930 align:middle line:84%
to believe that to
create in this world,

00:09:05.930 --> 00:09:09.420 align:middle line:84%
that we would have to ask that
come to pass on the one hand

00:09:09.420 --> 00:09:12.690 align:middle line:84%
rather than having the thoughts,
feelings, and the emotions

00:09:12.690 --> 00:09:18.320 align:middle line:84%
to allow creation to
build our hearts desire?

00:09:18.320 --> 00:09:19.720 align:middle line:84%
And clearly, this
mode of prayer,

00:09:19.720 --> 00:09:23.610 align:middle line:84%
it's not a wish machine,
it's not a mind control,

00:09:23.610 --> 00:09:25.860 align:middle line:84%
it's not leaving our
will on anything else.

00:09:25.860 --> 00:09:31.440 align:middle line:84%
It simply creates the pattern,
the template of a possibility

00:09:31.440 --> 00:09:35.180 align:middle line:84%
and allows that possibility
then to come to fruition.

00:09:35.180 --> 00:09:38.095 align:middle line:84%
>> So you really have to back
up when you say something like

00:09:38.095 --> 00:09:38.895 align:middle line:90%
this--

00:09:38.895 --> 00:09:39.695 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:09:39.695 --> 00:09:43.740 align:middle line:84%
>> --to the point that we are
actually part of the creative

00:09:43.740 --> 00:09:44.882 align:middle line:90%
energy.

00:09:44.882 --> 00:09:48.860 align:middle line:84%
>> We have, had, always,
and have today direct access

00:09:48.860 --> 00:09:51.830 align:middle line:84%
to the creative forces of our
world through a language that

00:09:51.830 --> 00:09:54.080 align:middle line:84%
until recently has been
poorly understood in the west.

00:09:54.080 --> 00:09:58.525 align:middle line:84%
That language is the union of
thought, feeling, and emotion,

00:09:58.525 --> 00:09:59.900 align:middle line:84%
which is so
fascinating, Corinne,

00:09:59.900 --> 00:10:01.473 align:middle line:84%
because in the
west, emotion, we've

00:10:01.473 --> 00:10:03.890 align:middle line:84%
done our best to get around
it, to get around the feelings

00:10:03.890 --> 00:10:05.180 align:middle line:90%
and emotions.

00:10:05.180 --> 00:10:08.360 align:middle line:84%
So we are a very logic
mental-based societies.

00:10:08.360 --> 00:10:12.380 align:middle line:84%
When you see old movies of
people praying or doing,

00:10:12.380 --> 00:10:14.130 align:middle line:84%
exercising their
powers, their thinking,

00:10:14.130 --> 00:10:17.310 align:middle line:84%
